<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900608-0059</DOCNO><DOCID>900608-0059.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Medtronic Inc.:   Company Sweetens Proposal   For Medical Pump Maker</HL><DATE>06/08/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   MDT BMDS</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)MEDICAL AND BIOTECHNOLOGY (MTC)</IN><LP>   Medtronic Inc. sweetened its stock swap proposal forBio-Medicus Inc., a maker of blood pumps used in surgery.   Under the new plan, the Minneapolis-based maker ofbiomedical devices is offering to exchange one Medtronicshare for 3.15 Bio-Medicus shares. Previously, it had beenproposing to swap one Medtronic share for 3.3 Bio-Medicusshares.</LP><TEXT>   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,Medtronic shares closed at $79.625, up 87.5 cents. UnderMedtronic's revised offer, that price would value eachBio-Medicus share at $25.278.   In national over-the-counter trading yesterday,Bio-Medicus shares jumped $1.375 to close at $23.125.   Medtronic has characterized its bid as friendly, butBio-Medicus's board met shortly after receiving the originalbid in mid-May and took no action on the proposal. Aspokesman said that Bio-Medicus's directors will meet toconsider the new proposal. He declined further comment.   Under a 1987 pact, Medtronic can't boost its current 5.5%stake in the company above 10% without Bio-Medicus boardapproval.</TEXT></DOC>